# ShellCheck configuration for spotx.sh
#
# spotx.sh deliberately uses several idioms that ShellCheck flags but that are
# correct for this script. The codes below are disabled project-wide so CI stays
# green while still catching genuinely new problem classes (parse errors,
# unhandled cd, dangerous redirects, etc.).
#
# SC2015 - "A && B || C": the script's pervasive conditional idiom (intentional).
# SC2016 - "$ in single quotes": Perl regex/one-liner payloads must NOT expand in shell.
# SC2034 - "appears unused": many vars are referenced indirectly via ${!name} or
#          inside eval'd (obfuscated) command strings ShellCheck cannot see.
# SC2059 - "variables in printf format": format args are color codes / versions /
#          paths with no '%' — benign here.
# SC2086 - "quote to prevent splitting": intentional where word-splitting is wanted
#          (e.g. `kill -9 ${spotifyPids}`); remaining hits are space-free paths.
# SC2155 - "declare and assign": return values of those command substitutions are
#          intentionally not inspected.
# SC2254 - unquoted $(...) in a case pattern (the date-gated developer flag).
# SC2027 - the `'"${var}"'` quoting idiom inside printf strings (intentional concat).
disable=SC2015,SC2016,SC2034,SC2059,SC2086,SC2155,SC2254,SC2027
